text: Brennand Airport, is a privately owned public use airport located southwest of the central business district of Neenah, a city in Winnebago County, Wisconsin, United States about halfway between Appleton and Oshkosh. The airport is home to EAA Chapter 41. Although most airports in the United States use the same three-letter location identifier for the FAA and International Air Transport Association (IATA), this airport is assigned 79C by the FAA but has no designation from the IATA. == Facilities and aircraft == Brennand Airport covers an area of at an elevation of 850 feet (259 m) above mean sea level. It has one asphalt runway: 18/36 is 2,450 by 30 feet (747 x 6 m). For the 12-month period ending July 11, 2017, the airport had 14,550 aircraft operations, an average of 40 per day; greater than 99% general aviation and less than 1% air taxi.
